"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The np.sinc function does not return 1 at x=0 and 0 at x=1. The np.sinc function returns sin(pi*x)/(pi*x) at x. At x=0, it returns 1, but at x=1, it does not return 0.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7,8c7,8\\n< assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n< assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[0], 1), \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], np.sinc(1)), \\\"Results not equal to np.sinc(1)\\\"\"\n}"